This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it presents a new network steganography method. It may also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it analyzes the network traffic generated by Google Suggest. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) as it deals with the manipulation of audio or visual data. It may also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it discusses the autocompletion of search phrases. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves the insertion of hidden data into a data structure.
